name: Salmon Teriyaki Kebabs
author: Anonymous
summary: This is a very easy and elegant way of serving much-loved and good-for-you salmon for a moist and delicious, low-carb dinner! Serve over rice, if desired.
ingredients: 1 tablespoon toasted sesame-ginger spice (such as Victoria Taylor's®)
1 ½ pounds salmon fillets, cut into cubes
2 medium green bell peppers, cut into large chunks
1 pint cherry tomatoes, or to taste
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, lemon juice, olive oil, honey, garlic powder, sesame-ginger spice, and sesame seeds in a large glass bowl
Add salmon, bell peppers, onion, and cherry tomatoes to the marinade
Marinate in the refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes
Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Thread salmon, bell peppers, onion, and tomatoes onto skewers and place on the prepared baking sheet
Cover wooden skewer ends with aluminum foil
Bake skewers in the preheated oven just until salmon flakes easily with a fork, about 10 minutes
